Subject:Re: [child_lit] Request for titles-loss, grieving, resilience
Missing May by Cynthia Rylant

Because of Winn Dixie by Kate di  Camillo

Esperanza Rising by Pam Munoz Ryan
(loss, immigration, transformational growth)


An unusual picture book for older students:

http://www.amazon.com/The-Little-Book-Happy-Sadness/dp/1933605901
the Big Little Book of Happy Sadness  by Colin Thompson


The Red Tree by Shaun Tan- (about depression)

Michael Rosen's Sad Book by Michael Rosen and Quentin Blake
(Michael Rosen's son died at age 18 and this book is about how he coped with it)




